title: Save the Date
description: Ms. Keane is nervous about a first date.

title: Knock It Off
description: When the Professor's college roommate sees his old pal's brilliant creations, he decides to cash in on the popularity of the Powerpuffs.

title: Not So Secret Service
description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

title: Worship
description: When the Fashionistas unveil their new mind controlling perfume, the Powerpuff Girls must find a way to stop them before Townsville falls under their spell.

title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

title: Telephonies/Tough Love
description: Telephonies: The Gangreen Gang gets hold of the Powerpuff Girls' Hotline and makes crank calls sending the Powerpuff Girls on a wild goose chases all over town./Tough Love: Everyone in Townsville loves the Powerpuff Girls! But the citizens have a sudden change of heart when Him sends out an evil gas turning the entire town against their favorite superheroes.

title: Can't Buy Love
description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

title: How to Draw Blossom
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Blossom.

title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

title: Secret Swapper of Doom
description: When the girls get a Paper Fortune Teller that can predict the future if they tell it a secret, they begin to rely on it to predict everything. But when it predicts the Powerpuff Girls will be destroyed, the girls must find a way to stop the future from happening.

title: Makes Zen to Me/Say Uncle
description: Makes Zen to Me: When Buttercup gets a fortune cookie saying peace lies within, the most violent of Powerpuffs sets out on a quest for inner peace./Say Uncle: The girls' go to pick up the Professor's brother at the train station, but mistake him for a wild-man being transported to the circus.

title: Bubbles' Beauty Blog But on Video
description: Bubbles' attempt to start her own beauty blog is thwarted by Blossom and Buttercup.

title: Small World: Maze Daze Part 3
description: The girls must enter a cursed jungle temple to obtain the last Heart Stone.

title: Air Buttercup
description: Buttercup tries to show off her basketball skills in the lunchroom to no avail.

title: Quarantine
description: After a chemical spill, the girls and Mojo find themselves trapped together.

title: Bubbs and Donny Get the Mail
description: Bubbles and Donny are given their most daring mission ever: get the mail.

title: Arachno Romance
description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

title: Superfriends
description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

title: All Chalked Up
description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

title: Man Up
description: When Buttercup's aggression inadvertently allows villain Man-Boy to escape, she starts a new-age lifestyle in an effort to be more calm. But when Man-Boy returns to enact his revenge, Buttercup must embrace the balance between punching and hugging in order to defeat him.

title: Twisted Sister/Cover Up
description: Twisted Sister: The girls decide they need some help fighting crime so they create another Powerpuff Girl. But they don't get the combination of sugar, spice and everything nice quite right./Cover Up: Blossom and Bubbles learn that Buttercup has secretly been rubbing a security blanket before every battle to make herself a super fighter. Can the girls convince Buttercup that her strength is within?

title: Something's a Ms./Slumbering with the Enemy
description: Something's a Ms: Miss Bellum is acting very strange lately. And she keeps showing up at crime scenes. Has our favorite secretary gone to the dark side, or is there another woman involved here?/Slumbering With The Enemy: When the girls decide to have an all-girl slumber party, a villain decides to crash it. To what lengths will this villain go to keep his identity hidden?

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup.

title: Buttercrush/Fuzzy Logic
description: Buttercrush: Buttercup falls for Ace, the leader of the Gangreen Gang. But when the gang exploits her infatuation to lure Blossom and Bubbles into danger, Buttercup shows them the real meaning of the word crush./Fuzzy Logic: Beastly bumpkin Fuzzy Lumkins goes wild in Townsville and only the Powerpuff Girls, with some help from a flying squirrel, can teach him to respect other people's property.

title: Rock Off Battle Music Video
description: The Powerpuff Girls rock out!

title: Mini Golf Madness
description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

title: Ping Pong Z
description: It's "loser does the dishes" when the girls play ping pong in and around Townsville.

title: In the Doghouse
description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

title: Little Octi Lost
description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

title: Clawdad
description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

title: Blundercup
description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

title: The Long Skate Home
description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

title: Silent Treatment/Sweet 'n' Sour
description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

title: The Bubbles-Sitters Club
description: Bubbles tries to prove that she's responsible enough to own a dog.

title: Bedtime
description: The girls need to get a good night's rest before family photo day, but they just can't seem to fall asleep!

title: Summer Bummer
description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

title: How to Draw Buttercup
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Buttercup.

title: Ragnarock and Roll
description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

title: Blossom3
description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom.

title: Largo
description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

title: Small World: Heart to Heartstone Part 4
description: In the stunning conclusion, the girls learn Lester has one more trick up his sleeve.

title: Small World: Stone Cold Spider Part 2
description: With Townsville in peril, the girls are sent to the arctic on a dangerous mission to find the key to saving the day.

title: Small World: Abra-Disaster Part 1
description: After defeating Mojo for the umpteenth time, the Powerpuff Girls are confident they are unstoppable.

title: Who's Got the Power?
description: Extended main title is set to music.

title: Moral Decay/Meet the Beat Alls
description: Moral Decay: When Bubbles loses a tooth, she gets a shiny coin under her pillow the next day. Buttercup sees a gold mine in the mouths of Townsville's criminal element./Meet the Beat Alls: Mojo, Him, Princess and Fuzzy band together to form the Bad Four, a criminal supergroup out to destroy the Powerpuff Girls. Everything is going great until Mojo meets Moko Jono and falls in love.

title: I'll Be Bake
description: Bubbles and Buttercup's good intentions are bad news for the cake Blossom is trying to bake.

title: Him Diddle Riddle
description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles.

title: Run, Blossom, Run
description: Blossom oversleeps and she'll stop at nothing to make it to school before she ruins her perfect attendance record!

title: Mojo the Great
description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

title: A Star is Blossom
description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

title: Trouble Clef
description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

title: How to Draw Bubbles
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Bubbles.

title: Mojo Builds a Shelf
description: Mojo discovers the only thing more difficult than total world domination is DIY furniture.

title: Blissfully Unaware
description: Bliss uses her telekinetic powers to help the Professor make a more delicious dinner.

title: Blue Ribbon Blues
description: When a famous scientist comes to the school, Blossom will stop at nothing to impress him at the Science Fair even if that means putting Townsville in danger!

title: Salamander
description: When the professor is kidnapped, the girls must go to a mysterious island to save him.

title: Birthday Bash/Too Pooped to Puff
description: Birthday Bash: It's the girls birthday and some special presents have arrived from the girls' main enemies. Can they destroy these evil gifts without destroying their party?/Too Pooped to Puff: The girls become exhausted when the town begins to over use them. They go on strike and end up teaching the townspeople how to fend for themselves.

title: Power-Noia
description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

title: Small World
description: After defeating Mojo for the umpteenth time, The Powerpuff Girls are confident they are unstoppable. With Townsville in peril, the girls are sent to the arctic on a dangerous mission to find the key to saving the day. The girls must enter a cursed jungle temple to obtain the last Heart Stone. In the stunning conclusion, the girls learn that Lester has one more trick up his sleeve.
